{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"adb4bcdf-5f34-4ade-a3b4-89165e138190","content":"The directory is empty, so I'll provide the recommended setup from MSTest knowledge:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` brings in the test framework, runner, and analyzers automatically.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings`)\n\nCreate a `my.runsettings` file (or add to your existing one):\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>  <!-- 0 = use number of CPU cores -->\n      <Scope>ClassLevel</Scope>\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nOr skip the file entirely and use the assembly-level attribute in a file like `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` ensures that class runs alone — no other tests execute concurrently with it.\n- You can apply it to as many classes as needed; they'll each run in isolation.\n- `Scope = ClassLevel` means methods *within* a non-decorated class can still run in parallel if you switch to `MethodLevel`, but `ClassLevel` is safer for most projects.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4edbe859-1c9c-4fdb-9e97-6940883eee06","outputTokens":497,"requestId":"800D:5D117:1678AFE:17E1286:6A046183"},"id":"039e99d5-34c7-47d7-a5c5-aa9d00ca030d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:33:37.760Z","parentId":"8dbcd